sentences.english: In the allness of the universe.
The totality of the purposefulness of that which we are, which transcends consciousness.
sentences.chinese: 那趨向完滿的我們的內在本質，它超越了意識。

sentences.english: The problem has been solved satisfactorily at last.
To live life to its fullest, each day must be created anew.
sentences.chinese: 爲了過一個完滿的人生，每一天都應該有所創造。

sentences.english: The music brought him a feeling of plenitude and freedom.
sentences.chinese: 這音樂帶給他一種完滿和自由的感覺。

sentences.english: Hong Kong Powerlifting Championships 2010 has been finished.
sentences.chinese: 香港健力錦標賽2010經已完滿結束。

sentences.english: The lecture ends in a sea of applauses.
sentences.chinese: 在一片雷鳴般的掌聲中，講座完滿結束。

sentences.english: Nice round number, as well-rounded as his game.
sentences.chinese: 完滿的數字，一如他的比賽，正變得成熟而全面。

sentences.english: The fullness of consumer enjoyment means fullness of life.
sentences.chinese: 消費者享受的完滿意味着生活的完滿。

sentences.english: The fullness of consumer enjoyment means fullness of life.
sentences.chinese: 消費者享受的完滿意味着生活的完滿。

sentences.english: Hong Kong Powerlifting Championships 2011 has been finished.
sentences.chinese: 香港健力錦標賽2011經已完滿結束。

sentences.english: He always picked the heavy loads and accomplished each task in full.
sentences.chinese: 他總是挑重擔子，完滿地完成每一項任務。

sentences.english: The pentagon is the most perfect graph.
sentences.chinese: 五角形是最完滿的圖形。

sentences.english: My young brother is illiterate. He was just celebrated for his one-month anniversary yesterday.
sentences.chinese: 我有個弟弟是個文盲，昨天剛做完滿月。

sentences.english: This is a difficult situation to which there is no perfectanswer.
sentences.chinese: 這是個困難的局面，並沒有一個完滿的答案。
